	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=182769"><span id=" ">Vymdraven the Malevolent</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">139 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.96]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Wizard ornate gloves have mana pres to SoS (at the time, incredibly useful). As for the focus effect, and the gloves being augmentable...As it is, these gloves provide 2 near useless effects. Wizard familiars give the vision enhancement. The dmg shield modifier doesn't do much for us either, since we rarely get into a situation where us tanking and having 3 extra pts of dmg shield on make any difference, except with green cons we can melee to death. <br/><br/>So I stand by my opinion that these gloves have bad focus effects on them for a wizard. The stats are good, which is fine, but if SOE is going to add focus effects, they should at least put some thought into class specific gear, and not copy paste itemization.<br/><br/>As for quest gear is concerned, with the focus effect on these gloves, I have to say that <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30800 newwindow target=akztarg>Desecrated Gloves of Order</a> are better, and these can be purchased in the bazaar, or gotten off of a common named mob in WoS, making these quest gloves not worth the risk / reward. But, if SOE modified the effect on the spelldeviser's gloves to something usefull to a wizard, it would make them desirable to quest for.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Nov 11 04:07:50 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Reality is the fantasy world in which we live - J. Tracy<br/>Vymdraven-Dark Elf Wizard<br/>Bertox<br/><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573242" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573242</a></td></tr>
